<cl=A2A2A2>
Sorcerers are the only magicians in Sphere who can provide objects with magical properties. The nature of this magic is alchemical, so sorcerers' knowledge of the magic of elements is poor. Sorcerers possess unique resistance to any kidns of attacks, physical or magical. Work with alchemical components and formulas does not leave them sufficient time to polishi their military skills. Those who are too keen on them and have gained any serious title are considered by Sorcerers ignorant and prevented from access to the Guild's knowledge. Sorcerers care about the guild's reputation very much, so they don't take up objects of dubious origin. Only weapons branded by Armorers or armor branded by Blacksmiths deserve their attention. Sorcerers have penetrated into the secret of armor so they have aquired an ability to influence them at a distance. The Tornado and Rusty Armor spells can at least give a Sorcerer enough time to disappear, if not change the course of battle.
<br>
